This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney aboard Air Force One en route to Newport News, Virginia. Carney discusses President Obama's visit to Newport News Shipbuilding, where he will discuss the impact of the sequester on the defense industry and the Virginia economy. Carney also addresses questions about the Taliban attacks in Afghanistan, the sequestration cuts, and a meeting between President Obama and Senators Graham and McCain. He emphasizes the need for a balanced approach to deficit reduction and criticizes Republican leaders for their unwillingness to compromise.